This place is at a convenient location in a big mall area with ample free parking and easy accessibility. The restaurant is a corner business at the restaurants area. The food display is very clean and has a nice presentation. The staff is usually very courteous and accommodating. The food is well prepared and they usually have a good variety of entrees to choose from. Overall the taste is good and very satisfying. The price is moderate considering it's an Express place (no waiters or waitress). A few gripes about this place. One being the utensils they use. They have bottom tier pre packaged utensils, but do not have bottom tier pricing. Wendy's has better utensils than this place those. I really wish owners of these places would pay attention to the details that really make the experience at the place much more pleasant to the patrons. It really sucks to have to cut your Yuca with a bending knife, and to try and get your ropa vieja with a twisting fork. It literally almost entirely depletes the joy of being able to eat a great meal in heavenly enjoyment when you have to shift your focus from the flavors, to having to craft your meal with the subpar cutlery. We need more available table salt, enough to not have to wait for someone else to finish using it. We need an easier, more available way to be able to have water without having to actually purchase water, or have to wait online to ask for a cup for water (which often gets challenged bc there's a fountain machine with sodas available). I'm certain there's a law regarding this. Perhaps including a small water bottle with every meal upon request given the price being paid (Pruzzo's Deli includes a 16 oz. Kirkland water bottle with the purchase of any deli sandwich or hot meal at no additional cost) I'm sure that although it may increase your expense by a few dollars per case, it will greatly increase your revenue overall bc more people will know they will have a more affordable complete meal here. There tends to be a lot of clutter in the passage/hallway that leads to the back once you pass the fountain machine. It's a bit of an eyesore. This feedback is actually constructive, and most business would love to have it. So I will say you're welcome for the feedback and I look forward to the possibility of these improvements being implemented. Prioritize on the utensils though. That would be greatly appreciated. Next time I come around, I'll be looking for the change. If I see it, I'll update the review and add another star. Overall a good place to have a nice meal, despite the above. I recommend.
